						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone couch kept in a room in the compound of Madhukēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Raghu—16th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vibhava, Māgha, Śu, Śivarātri, Wednesday.</hi> On palaeographical grounds, the record may be assigned to the 16th century.</p>						

						<p>The inscription in Sanskrit verse, states that the stone couch was presented to god Madhukēśvara of <hi rend="bold">Jayantipura,</hi> for use in the spring festival, by <hi rend="bold">Raghu,</hi> the king of <hi rend="bold">Sōdā.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
